<item>
            <title>[LU-2100] ofd batched precreation exceeds transaction on small devices</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2100</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;on small devices (like used with local configuration) and ldiskfs ofd batched pre-creation can exceed transaction causing a lot of messages like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lustre: 13034:0:(osd_handler.c:697:osd_trans_start()) lustre-OST0000: too many transaction credits (3191 &amp;gt; 1024)&lt;br/&gt;
LustreError: 13034:0:(osd_handler.c:708:osd_trans_start())   attr_set: 0, punch: 0, xattr_set: 0,&lt;br/&gt;
LustreError: 13034:0:(osd_handler.c:711:osd_trans_start())   create: 127, ref_add: 0, ref_del: 0, write: 1&lt;br/&gt;
LustreError: 13034:0:(osd_handler.c:714:osd_trans_start())   insert: 0, delete: 0, destroy: 0&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
